ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Blood cadmium (ug/L)
Indicator - blood cadmium below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.1 ug/L; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: Blood manganese (ug/L)
Indicator - blood manganese below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.99 ug/L; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: Blood lead (ug/dL)
Indicator - blood lead below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.07 ug/dL; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: Blood selenium (ug/L)
Indicator - blood selenium below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 24.48 ug/l; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: Total blood mercury (ug/L)
Indicator - total blood mercury below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.28 ug/L; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: blood ethyl mercury (ug/L)
Indicator - blood ethyl mercury below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.16 ug/L; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: blood methyl mercury (ug/L)
Indicator - blood methyl mercury below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.12 ug/L; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing

ElementDescription: blood inorganic mercury (ug/L)
Indicator - blood inorganic mercury below limit of detection
Notes: LOD = 0.27 ug/L; 0 = not below LOD; 1 = below LOD; -9 = missing
